<dl id="n25071a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25071a">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25071a"> 71(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> column</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When the <mark>column</mark> of the Imperial Guard made their great charge at the end of the day, the troops of Foy&apos;s division advanced in support of them, and Colonel Lemonnier Delafosse describes the confident hopes of victory and promotion with which he marched to that attack, and the fearful carnage and confusion of the assailants, amid which he was helplessly hurried back by his flying comrades. <small> Edward Creasy, <a name="ECFD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECFD"><cite title="source">The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World</cite></a> (1915) 438</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14042c" href="c14all.htm#c14042c">VI.C.14:042(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
